Chaos erupted in Alexandra township on Tuesday over food parcels. Residents queued outside a school but the delivery never happened. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Chaos erupted in Alexandra township on Tuesday over food parcels. Residents queued outside a school but the delivery never happened. WATCH: Mitchells Plain residents clash with police over food parcels Ignoring lockdown rules to stay at their homes, residents did not keep any social distancing as they waited. The police had to disperse the angry crowd. Meanwhile, Johannesburg Mayor Geoff Makhubo says the city will address the situation. He has called for NGOs to contact the city before distributing food parcels. Applications for food parcels can be made by calling the National @OfficialSASSA Call Centre 0800601011 or sending an email to grantenquiries@sassa.gov.za - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.